Task 5: Bootstrap Framework

Bootstrap is a popular CSS framework that provides pre-built HTML and CSS components for building responsive web designs. It includes a grid system, typography, forms, buttons, and more.

Example of a simple web layout using Bootstrap:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
  <title>Bootstrap Example</title>
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg bg-body-tertiary">
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <a class="navbar-brand" href="#">Navbar</a>
      <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#navbarNav" aria-controls="navbarNav" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
        <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNav">
        <ul class="navbar-nav">
          <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link active" aria-current="page" href="#">Home</a>
          </li>
          <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link" href="#">Features</a>
          </li>
          <li class="nav-item">
            <a class="nav-link" href="#">Pricing</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <h2>Hello, world!</h2>
        <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.</p>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Primary</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary">Secondary</button>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6">
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>

Bootstrap classes used:

- navbar: Creates a navbar component.
- container: Creates a container to center content.
- row: Creates a row within the grid system.
- col-md-6: Creates a column that spans 6 columns on medium and larger screens.
- btn: Creates a button.
- btn-primary, btn-secondary: Styles the buttons.